         <abstract>
            <p>A detailed comparison is made between a continued fraction of Gauss, and one of Perron, for the evaluation of ratios of modified Bessel functions $I_\nu(x)/I_{\nu-1}(x), x &gt; 0, \nu &gt; 0$. It will be shown that Perron's continued fraction has remarkable advantages over Gauss' continued fraction, particularly when $x \gg \nu$.</p>
          </abstract>
